170
00:11:26,460 --> 00:11:30,040
Umm, today... today...

171
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:34,990
Today I skipped school with Arashiyama and hung out.

172
00:11:35,020 --> 00:11:37,490
Huh? Was that all?

173
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:42,620
Guess I should read this novel to improve my writing skills.

174
00:11:42,620 --> 00:11:44,970
Even though I know the perp already.

175
00:11:44,970 --> 00:11:46,890
Book title: "1/4th Murderous Intent"

176
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:50,000
If love were a drink...

177
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:53,610
Love would be a delicious coffee.

178
00:11:53,620 --> 00:11:56,230
The bitter flavor gives a the sleepless night

179
00:11:56,230 --> 00:11:59,080
in exchange for dependence and peace of mind.

180
00:11:59,090 --> 00:12:01,560
Arashiyama - cold one.

181
00:12:01,570 --> 00:12:02,440
Huh?

182
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:07,190
But if there's a mistake, it becomes a misunderstanding.

183
00:12:07,220 --> 00:12:09,270
What the heck? Who's a cold one?

184
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,590
Did you forget the name of your childhood friend?!

185
00:12:11,590 --> 00:12:12,440
Huh?

186
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:15,330
Calm down! Arashiyama, "cold one" is...

187
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:18,080
What?! Who's a cold one?

188
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:21,700
Sanada, you use pretty old words don't you.

189
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:22,410
Wha?

190
00:12:22,410 --> 00:12:24,340
Get out!!

191
